1. For the lentils, put them in a saucepan, cover with water, bring to a boil the reduce the heat and simmer for about 15â€“20 minutes, or until all the liquid has evaporated and the lentils are not mushy and still with a bite. 2. As soon as the lentils are cooked transfer them to a large bowl and leave to cool. 3. Once the lentils are cool, add the beetroot, spring onions, hazelnuts and herbs and stir until everything is combined. 4. For the dressing, put the ginger, mustard, oil and vinegar in a bowl and, using a hand-held blender, blend until combined. 5. Drizzle the dressing over the salad and serve.